{
  "name": "Explosion of Rot",
  "type": "spell",
  "effects": [],
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p>A giant pustule swells and explodes, coating everything around it in life-draining rot. Creatures in the area take 6d6 poison damage and must attempt a basic Reflex save. Foliage and plant matter in the area no longer counts as cover after this spell affects it.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Critical Success</strong> The target is unaffected.</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong> The target takes half damage.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> The target takes full damage and is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.MIRkyAjyBeXivMa7]{Enfeebled 1}.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> The target takes double damage, @Damage[floor((@item.level -2)/2)d6[persistent,poison]] damage, and is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.MIRkyAjyBeXivMa7]{Enfeebled 2}.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Heightened (+2)</strong> The initial damage increases by 2d6, and the persistent damage increases by 1d6.</p>"
    },
